testsuite.name: graphql.execution.ExecutionStrategyTest

testcase.name: complete values always calls query strategy to execute more
completes value for a java.util.List
completes value for java.util.Optional
completes value for an empty java.util.Optional that triggers non null exception
completes value for java.util.OptionalInt
completes value for an empty java.util.OptionalInt that triggers non null exception
completes value for java.util.OptionalDouble
completes value for an empty java.util.OptionalDouble that triggers non null exception
completes value for java.util.OptionalLong
completes value for an empty java.util.OptionalLong that triggers non null exception
completes value for an array
completing value with serializing throwing exception
completing enum with serializing throwing exception
completing a scalar null value for a non null type throws an exception
resolveField creates correct DataFetchingEnvironment
test that the new data fetcher error handler interface is called
test that the old legacy method is still useful for those who derive new execution strategies
#522 - single error during execution - not two errors
#163 completes value for an primitive type array
#820 processes DataFetcherResult
#1558 forward localContext on nonBoxed return from DataFetcher
#820 processes DataFetcherResult just message
completes value for an iterable
when completeValue expects GraphQLList and non iterable or non array is passed then it should yield a TypeMismatch error
